            <h4>Advisory Council:</h4>
            <p>
            The Advisory Council is composed of eminent scholars with an established international reputation. They hold position of eminence in the field of sphere of activity of the GVF. They provide guidance and direction for the appropriate course of action for the GVF.
            </p>
             <h4>Board of Trustee:</h4>
            <p>
            The Board of Trustees is responsible for the overall organization and working of the GVF. It formulates broader policies on which the GVF ought to work. The Trustees have experience and expertise in different areas in which the GVF possesses core expertise.
            </p> 
            <h4>Governing Body:</h4>
            <p>
            The Governing Body is responsible for the day-to-day operation of the GVF. It is responsible for implementation of the objectives of the Trust and activities specifically dedicated by the Board of Trustees for implementation.
            </p> 
            <h4>Fellows:</h4>
            <p>
            Fellows are experts in respective fields who are a part of groups working on different topics. They are involved either in an honorary or permanent capacity. Most of the Fellows in honorary capacity are academics and scholars working in different education and research institutions. The uniqueness of the Fellows of the GVF is that it even comprises of experts from industry with immense practical experience. The body of fellows is thus a meeting point of theoretical knowledge as well as practical experience.
            </p> 
            <h4>Researchers:</h4>
            <p>
            The GVF employs some researchers on full time and is also associated with other researches who volunteer to work for the GVF.
            </p>
